        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-21T01:24:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yep, this was on my mental todo list because I wanted to mull over what the best response to a bad address range would actually be. It\u0027s probably more likely that something in our parsing went wrong and gave us bad addresses, in which case logging an error and returning false is the way to go. If  this is actually the result of the kernel giving us a bad address range, does that indicate a serious enough corruption that we actually want to give up? Or still keep on collecting information? In general, do we consider apparent errors from the kernel/OS/anything outside the target process outside the scope of what Crashpad should dissect?",
      "parentUuid": "bef57937_8c53a3f6",
      "revId": "f7ccd101a1c0370793694ee82e9ead05b60f7057",
