      "message": "Ah, good approximation!\n\nInstead of |index| and |name|, you can pass field[index] and \u0026mapping.name to the macro, and then it looks and behaves more like a function. You don’t actually have to make it a function: you can keep it a macro so that it’s allowed to return from Initialize() without any help. It’s just a little easier to read and think about a macro that behaves more like a function than not.",
